  "prompt": "In no more than 200 words please describe a time you gave remarkable service to one of your customer?",
  "response": "During a particularly busy holiday season at my retail job, a customer approached me in distress. She had forgotten a gift for her daughter\u2019s birthday that was only a few hours away. After listening to her plight, I quickly assessed our inventory and discovered we were out of stock on popular toys. I asked her about her daughter\u2019s interests and suggested a custom gift basket using available items in the store. I gathered a selection of toys, books, and treats that matched her daughter\u2019s preferences and arranged them beautifully.\n\nTo ensure she could make it to the party on time, I offered to wrap the basket and even included a handwritten card. Despite the rush, I prioritized her order and completed it in record time. The customer was overwhelmed with gratitude when she saw the finished product. She left the store with a huge smile and expressed how much my efforts meant to her. A few days later, I received a heartfelt thank-you note from her, sharing how her daughter loved the gift. This experience reinforced the impact of going above and beyond to provide exceptional service.",
